# Service Layer Rules

When modifying files in `src/services/`:

## Required Patterns
- Every service file MUST have: `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)`
- Every service class receives `db: AsyncSession` via constructor, never creates sessions
- External API calls MUST be wrapped in try/except with error classification
- Tool methods return `{"success": True, "data": {...}}` or `{"success": False, "error": "..."}`

## Forbidden Patterns
- NEVER import from `src/routers/` (this breaks the layer architecture)
- NEVER use `print()` — use `logger.info()`, `logger.warning()`, `logger.error()`
- NEVER create database engines directly — use dependency injection

## When Adding a New Service
Run the scaffolding generator instead of creating files manually:
```bash
python scripts/new_service.py <platform_name> --with-router --with-tools
```

## After Changes
```bash
python scripts/verify_architecture.py
python scripts/verify_tools.py
pytest tests/test_<service_name>.py -v
```
